    "are set to 20 million and 2, respectively.",
    "Range Query Generation.",
    "We first randomly sample S = 100 points from a given dataset X as the lower corners of query boxes.",
    "Then, for each dimension i = 1, • • •, d, a random width δ i is added to the lower corner to create the upper corner.",
    "For a generated query box R, the selectivity of R is defined as the percentage of points in X covered by R, i.e.,sel(R) = |{x | x ∈ X ∧ R covers x}| |X |."
